This paper discusses cyber security and the use of deception techniques to mislead infiltrators. The paper uses a game-theoretic approach to model the interaction between the deceiver and the infiltrator, which suggests that it belongs to the cs.GT (Game Theory) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of AI techniques to compute optimal strategies for the deceiver and the infiltrator, which suggests that it belongs to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of robust optimization techniques, which suggests that it belongs to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of these techniques in the context of network security, which suggests that it belongs to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-categories.
